<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10640</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr><route>erct-002A.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10641</anchor>  <addr>erct-003R</addr><route>erct-003R.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › propositional truncation and existence</title>  <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10642</anchor> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0028</addr><route>erct-0028.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositional truncation</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex> we have a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex> equipped with a unit map <tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">propositions</link> <tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</tex>, any function <tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> extends to a function <tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</tex>.</p><p>When we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>, we will say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10643</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr><route>erct-002A.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10644</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr><route>erct-0029.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10645</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003F</addr><route>erct-003F.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Bijection</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003F.agda" type="external">erct-003F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>bijective</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10646</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr><route>erct-0029.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>